(188, 3, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p><img class=" size-full wp-image-185" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Peterheadshot_twitter.jpg" width="360" height="270" alt="Peterheadshot_twitter" style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial;" width="360" height="270" /> <img class=" size-full wp-image-186" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/vanderkolkportret1.jpg" width="196" height="270" alt="Bessel van der Kolk Pic" style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial;" width="1456" height="2008" /></p> <p><img class=" size-full wp-image-187" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Meadows_plain_2011lg.png" width="500" height="125" alt="Meadows logo" width="864" height="216" /></p> <p>Thanks to The <a style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial; font-size: 16px;" target="_blank" title="The Meadows Homepage" href="http://www.themeadows.org/">Meadows Addiction Treatment Center</a>,&nbsp;Dr. Levine will be doing two events on the Eastern Seaboard this September, based on his best-selling book - In an Unspoken Voice, How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness. He will be joined in Boston by trauma pioneer, Bessel van der Kolk, M.D.</p> <p>These presentations, designed for therapists, but approachable by all, will be a whirlwind tour, starting at the very beginnings of the animal world, through human development and our developing nervous system, onto the ethological connections to trauma. Several case studies and video examples will be shown in this dynamic and exciting events - one of my favorites.&nbsp;</p> <p>Bessel van der Kolk is a premiere researcher on trauma, author of the seminal book <em><a target="_blank" title="Link to Dr. van der Kolk\'s work" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=23:traumatic-stress-the-effects-of-overwhelming-experience-on-mind-body-and-society-by-bessel-a-van-der-kolk&amp;catid=11&amp;Itemid=4">Traumatic Stress</a></em></p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Find info and register for New York" href="http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992641">New York City</a>&nbsp;</p> <p>AMA theater on 7th Avenue, will be on September 16.</p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Find info and register for Boston, Mass" href="http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992653">Boston</a></p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Find info and register for Boston, Mass" href="http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992653"></a>featuring Bessel van der Kolk, author of the seminal book, Traumatic Stress, &nbsp;September 23rd.</p> <p> </p>', 'Dr. Levine presents in Boston and NY this September!', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'dr-levine-presents-in-boston-and-ny-this-september', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/?p=188', 15, 'post', '', 0),
(189, 3, '2011-09-23 20:07:44', '2011-09-23 20:07:44', '<p><a target="_blank" title="Priscilla Warner\'s blog" href="http://priscillawarnerbooks.com">Priscilla Warner</a>, Author of <em><a title="Her books Amazon page - because we appreciate the free promotion." href="http://www.amazon.com/Learning-Breathe-Yearlong-Quest-Bring/dp/1439181071/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1318165624&amp;sr=1-1">Learning to Breathe</a>&nbsp;</em>was interviewed by Ann Curry on NBC\'s <a target="_blank" title="The Today Show Video timeline - Ms. Warner is at 8:40am Sept 23rd,2011" href="http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/35133959/ns/today/t/watch-latest-today-video/">Today Show</a>, and talked about her book and her year-long journey to overcome anxiety. The subject of trauma came up, and she shared that she used EMDR and "another wonderful, exciting therapy called Somatic Experiencing."&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p> </p> <p>So, we are excited by this very public mention, and present it to you here.&nbsp;</p> <p>Check it out.&nbsp;</p> <p> <object codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=10,0,32,18" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="245" width="420"> <param name="FlashVars" value="launch=44638468&amp;width=420&amp;height=245" /> <param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /> <param name="wmode" value="transparent" /> <param name="src" value="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/32545640" /><embed height="245" width="420" src="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/32545640" wmode="transparent" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" flashvars="launch=44638468&amp;width=420&amp;height=245" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"></embed> </object> </p> <p style="font-size: 11px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #999; margin-top: 5px; background: transparent; text-align: center; width: 420px;">Visit msnbc.com for <a style="text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;" href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com">breaking news</a>, <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3032507" style="text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;">world news</a>, and <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3032072" style="text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;">news about the economy</a></p>', 'Priscilla Warner mentions trauma therapy on Today show', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'priscilla-warner-mentions-trauma-therapy-on-today-show', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:28:55', '2014-09-29 18:28:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/2011/09/23/priscilla-warner-mentions-trauma-therapy-on-today-show/', 1, 'post', '', 0),
