(207, 3, '2013-01-29 20:42:29', '2013-01-29 20:42:29', '<p align="center" style="line-height: 150%; text-align: left;">Dr. Levine will be in London, England from May 25th to the 26th for the Breath of Life Conference for 2013. This Conference is for Cranial Sacral Therapists, and we are proud to be in partnership with them.</p> <p align="center" style="line-height: 150%; text-align: left;">Dr. Levine will be presenting a keynote, entitled:&nbsp;<a href="#keynote"><b style="line-height: 150%;">Spirituality and Trauma: From Trauma to Awakening and Flow</b></a> as well as a 2 day Post Conference Workshop, entitled: <a href="#workshop"><strong><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">Emotional Self-Regulation: the Body and Change</span></strong></a><a href="#workshop"><strong>Working with Difficult Feelings</strong></a>(Click each link for a short description).&nbsp;</p> <p>The Breath of Life enrollment is available directly through their website. For More information and to enroll, please visit the&nbsp;<a href="http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/" title="Breath of Life London\'s website." target="_blank">Breath of Life conference website</a></p> <p>Click Read More:</p> <p> <!--more--> </p> <h6 align="center" style="line-height: 1.2em; font-size: 1.2em;"><a name="keynote">Spirituality and Trauma;&nbsp;From Trauma to Awakening and Flow</a></h6> <p>In the treatment of the effects of trauma, its inherent relationship with spirituality provides a vital link in the therapeutic process.&nbsp; The understanding of a person\'s, felt, spiritual connection is central to the therapeutic process.&nbsp; If we are unable to access a person\'s spirituality, we may find ourselves trapped, as therapists, in areas that are fraught with pitfalls and "tight corners".&nbsp; The intimate association between trauma and spirituality suggests therapeutic avenues that support the authentic transformation of traumatic experiences.</p> <p style="line-height: 150%;"><a href=".../images/stories/articles/bol-2013_UK/bol_large.jpg" title="Link to larger image" target="_blank"><img class=" size-full wp-image-205" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bol_small.jpg" width="196" height="277" alt="breath of life small" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; padding: 4px; border: 2px solid #246da5;" width="196" height="277" /></a></p> <p style="line-height: 150%;">&nbsp;</p> <p style="line-height: 150%;">Through the use of didactic material- including brain research, experiential practice incorporating the bodily "felt-sense", and video material, we will introduce Somatic Experiencing® as a way to re-connect with the deep self. &nbsp; The focus will be on developing practical tools to gracefully enhance the relationship between trauma and spirituality within the therapeutic experience. &nbsp;</p> <p style="line-height: 150%;">You can see the event listing from our <a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/event-calendar.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=10" title="Our event listing" target="_blank">website</a>, or head directly to <a href="http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/" title="Breath of Life Homepage" target="_blank">BOL\'s website</a>.&nbsp;</p> <p><br /> <br /><a name="workshop"></a></p> <h6 align="center" style="line-height: 1.2em; font-size: 1.2em;"><a name="workshop">Emotional Self-Regulation: the Body and ChangeWorking with Difficult Feelings</a></h6> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>In doing therapeutic work, therapists are often confused about the role of emotions. Sometimes therapists and body-workers have the idea that they are supposed to avoid emotions, and others may have been trained to “go after them—to get them out.”</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>While it is true that intense emotional eruptions can interfere with one’s life, there is a deeper truth: that helping clients access their natural emotions, and learn from them, is an important part of good depth therapy and an enhancement to life.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Emotional self-regulation, as we shall explore together, is essential to lasting integration and wholeness. In this regard we will explore how certain emotions (such as disgust and anger) are “gatekeepers” and are essential to opening to other feelings which, together, promotes a fuller, wiser, vital and creative life.</p> <p>See the <a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/bol_conf_flyer1.pdf" title="Breath of Life Flyer" target="_blank">Flyer here</a>. Or go to our <a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/event-calendar.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=11" title="SE.com\'s event listing" target="_blank">Event listing for location info</a>, or head directly to <a href="http://breathoflifeconference.co.uk/?page_id=491" title="Breath of Life workshop page" target="_blank">BOL\'s website</a> to enroll</p>', 'Breath of Life Conference - This May in London, UK', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'breath-of-life-conference-this-may-in-london-uk', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:28:33', '2014-09-29 18:28:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/2013/01/29/breath-of-life-conference-this-may-in-london-uk/', 8, 'post', '', 0),
(208, 3, '2013-01-29 21:54:09', '2013-01-29 21:54:09', '<p align="center"><img src="https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/Gallery/attachment_hero.jpg" alt="UCLA Conference - Attachment and Neuroplasticity" style="border: 2px solid #246da5; display: block; padding: 4px;" /></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>We are happy to announce that March 8th through the 10th, Dr. Levine has been invited to speak at UCLA\'s Extension and Lifespan Learning Institute\'s conference; entitled - How People Change: Relationships and Neuroplasticity in Psychotherapy.</p> <p>This presentation is open to the public. For more information, <a href="https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/default.aspx" title="UCLA Extension website" target="_blank">please visit here:</a></p> <p><a href="https://www.uclaextension.edu/attachment/Pages/Gallery/2013%20Attachment%20Conference%20Brochure.pdf" title="Conference Brochure" target="_blank">PDF brochure is here:</a>&nbsp;</p> <p><a href="http://maps.ucla.edu/campus/?locid=83759" title="UCLA interactive map" target="_blank">Located in the Ackerman Grand Ballroom</a>. (Link will take you to a lovely interactive map of UCLA\'s campus). You\'re welcome.</p>', 'UCLA Presents - How People Change: Relationships and Neuroplasticity in Psychotherapy', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'ucla-presents-how-people-change-relationships-and-neuroplasticity-in-psychotherapy', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:28:33', '2014-09-29 18:28:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/2013/01/29/ucla-presents-how-people-change-relationships-and-neuroplasticity-in-psychotherapy/', 7, 'post', '', 0),
