(211, 3, '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '2013-01-30 00:21:29', '<p align="center"><a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/se_masterclass-bw_pv_syndromes_apr_20131.pdf" title="See the Flyer (PDF)" target="_blank"><img class=" size-full wp-image-210" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Polyvagal-syndromes2.jpg" alt="Polyvagal-syndromes2" style="border: 2px solid #246da5; display: block; padding: 4px;" width="750" height="300" width="750" height="300" /></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>The Somatic Experiencing® Trauma Institute is proud to present another in a series of post advanced courses, taught by Dr. Peter A Levine. These classes are designed to enhance and extend your skillsets that you have been developing in the 3 year SE® Training.&nbsp;<br /><br />Location: <a href="http://book.bestwestern.com/bestwestern/US/CA/Corte-Madera-hotels/BEST-WESTERN-PLUS-Corte-Madera-Inn/Hotel-Overview.do?propertyCode=05259" title="Corte Madera Inn\'s homepage." target="_blank">Corte Madera Best Western Inn</a> -&nbsp;56 Madera Blvd &nbsp;Corte Madera, CA 94925</p> <p>Dates: April 18th-22nd, 2013</p> <p>Price: $1495 ($200 if you sign up before March 18th!)</p> <p>How to Enroll: Call 303-652-4035 or email <a href="mailto:info@traumahealing.com">info@traumahealing.com</a>&nbsp;(subject: Master Class Enrollement)</p> <p>Click "Read More" to the right to see the class description</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>  <!--more-->  <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div style="background-color: #c9c9c9; color: #2c1dgf; font-size: 12pt; font-family: Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica, San-serif;"> <p style="text-align: center;">Advanced Bodywork, Polyvagal Theory, and Complex Syndromes</p> <p style="text-align: center;">A Master Class With SE Founder</p> <p style="text-align: center;">Peter A Levine, PhD</p> <p>The Polyvagal Theory of Stephen Porges, PhD, is a critically important neuro-scientific map for informing precise Somatic Experiencing® interventions. This is particularly true when working directly with SE® bodywork. Porges’ theory guides us in precisely assessing where a client is stuck so that we can support their movement out of shutdown and numbness, to contained arousal, and then to establish core equilibrium, social engagement and enduring feelings of presence, vitality and goodness. Preparing you, the therapist, to competently achieve these lofty (though attainable) goals is the aim of this Master Class.</p> <p>In addition, we will delve into how SE® based bodywork can treat complex syndromes caused by core autonomic dysregulation. These syndromes include migraines, asthma, fibromyalgia, Irritable Bowel Syndrome, Chronic Fatigue Syndrome, Regional Complex Pain Syndrome, as well as, low heart rate or blood pressure, certain cardiac arrhythmias, light headedness, fainting (syncope), and a variety of auto-immune diseases. You will learn why individuals frequently present with these problematic and mutating symptoms, and how they are also associated with various anxiety disorders and depressive conditions. We will expand upon our basic SE® techniques and discover how to treat these syndromes as a cohesive whole. The class will be a mixture of didactic lecture, live demonstrations and hands-on experiential practice.</p> <p>While this training is primarily for individuals who have completed their advanced level training by the time of the master class, it will also be opened to a few skilled body workers who have completed their intermediate level training. While the focus of this special class is on advanced applications of SE Bodywork, it is also open to psycho therapists with some bodywork experience who are wishing to advance their skills.</p> <p><em>Suggested Preparation</em></p> <p>It is important to have (re) read chapters 5&amp;6 in: <a href="http://www.amazon.com/In-Unspoken-Voice-Releases-Restores/dp/1556439431/ref=pd_bxgy_b_img_y" title="Amazon Page for In an Unsoken Voice" target="_blank">In an Unspoken Voice; How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness</a>. Additionally, it would be useful to review some of Dr. Porges book: <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Polyvagal-Theory-Neurophysiological-Communication-Self-regulation/dp/0393707008" title="Amazon page for Polyvagal Theory" target="_blank">The Polyvagal Theory: Neurophysiological Foundations of Emotions, Attachment, Communication, and Self-regulation</a> (Norton Series on Interpersonal Neurobiology)</p> </div>', 'UPDATED---Advanced Bodywork, Polyvagal Theory, and Complex Syndromes - Master Class in Corte Madera, Ca', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'advanced-bodywork-polyvagal-theory-and-complex-syndromes-master-class-in-corte-madera-ca', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:28:33', '2014-09-29 18:28:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/2013/01/30/advanced-bodywork-polyvagal-theory-and-complex-syndromes-master-class-in-corte-madera-ca/', 5, 'post', '', 0),
(212, 3, '2013-01-30 01:16:38', '2013-01-30 01:16:38', '<p>One of Peter\'s classic videos - Jody, My Ears, My Tears and My Fears, is one of the seminal training videos in the Somatic Experiencing®.&nbsp;</p> <h3>Jody-</h3> <p>&nbsp;</p> <br /> <iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/58570494" width="500" height="375" frameborder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>', 'Jody - My Ears, My Tears, My Fears', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'jody-my-ears-my-tears-my-fears', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:28:33', '2014-09-29 18:28:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/2013/01/30/jody-my-ears-my-tears-my-fears/', 4, 'post', '', 0),
(213, 3, '2013-02-04 23:35:39', '2013-02-04 23:35:39', '<p><a href="http://www.womenssymposium.org/index.php" title="Go to Register Now" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.womenssymposium.org/images/2013-save-the-date.jpg" alt="Womens Symposium Save the Date" width="300" height="170" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /></a></p> <p>Dr. Levine will be participating as a speaker at the 2013 Women’s Symposium. The Women’s Symposium is a one-day event featuring women leaders in the field of addiction, behavioral health, and women’s issues. Our 2013 Women’s Symposium message is a “Journey to Wholeness.”<span style="line-height: 1.3em;">&nbsp;This year’s topics are practical, solution-focused and designed to enrich the skills of professionals within the field of addiction treatment and those who treat addicted women.</span></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Check out their site for <a href="http://www.womenssymposium.org/index.php" title="Women\'s Symposium Homepage" target="_blank">more info.</a></p>', 'Speaking at the Betty Ford Center\'s Women\'s Symposium  on March 21st at UCLA', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'speaking-at-the-betty-ford-centers-womens-symposium-on-march-21st-at-ucla', '', '', '2014-09-29 11:28:33', '2014-09-29 18:28:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/2013/02/04/speaking-at-the-betty-ford-centers-womens-symposium-on-march-21st-at-ucla/', 6, 'post', '', 0) ;
