(364, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg" title="Full Size"><img class=" size-full wp-image-190" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg" width="200" height="200" alt="Case_consult" width="612" height="612" /></a></p> <p>The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and demonstrations with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner." </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p> </p> <p>Please contact Joan Luly for <a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/caseconsultflyer1.pdf" target="_blank">more information</a>: joansehealing@mac.com. Also, view our PDF\'s for <a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/registration_form.pdf" target="_blank">sign up forms</a> and information about submitting as a demo client.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>', 'See Peter Work in San Diego, November 5th', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 193, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(365, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/LA_consult_flyer_v3-mar-2013_web1.pdf" title="Consult Flyer" target="_blank"><span style="line-height: 1.3em;"><img class=" size-full wp-image-203" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/LA_consult_flyer_v3-mar-2013_web1.pdf" width="150" height="194" alt="LA consult flyer v3-mar-2013 web" style="padding: 4px; border: 2px solid #246da5;" width="" height="" /></span></a></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="line-height: 1.3em;">The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and supervision with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</span></p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner." </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p>&nbsp;<a href="index.php?option=com_eventbooking&amp;view=category&amp;Itemid=110" title="Event Page" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Only the waiting list is available. Click here.</strong></span></a></p> <ul> <li><a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/consult-registration.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=1">All Day Registration</a>: (11am-6pm, worth 2 Consult Hours)<span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong></strong></span></li> <li><a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/consult-registration.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=3">Afternoon (2nd half) Registration</a>: (3pm-6pm, worth 1 Consult Hour)</li> <li><a href="https://somaticexperiencing.com/events/consult-registration.html?task=view_event&amp;event_id=2">Morning (1st Half) Registration</a>:&nbsp;(11am-2pm, worth 1 Consult Hour)</li> </ul> <p>Please contact Victoria Mihich for <a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/LA_consult_flyer_v3-mar-2013_web1.pdf" target="_blank">more information</a>: <a href="mailto:%20Victoria4PeterLevine@yahoo.com">Victoria4PeterLevine@yahoo.com</a>.</p> <p>If you are interested in having Peter see a client of yours, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href="mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com">traumahealing@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;with the following information:</p> <ol> <li>First name and age of client.</li> <li>Brief list of relevant trauma history (Including the age that it occurred)</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is stuck.</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is advancing.</li> <li>Why do you specifically want Peter to see this client.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <p>NOTE: NO cancellations can be made after March 20th, 2013. Thank you.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>', 'UPDATED***Peter Levine Group Case Consultation in Los Angeles - March 23rd! - Sold Out', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '204-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 204, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/204-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(366, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg" title="Full Size"><img class=" size-full wp-image-190" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Case_consult.jpg" width="200" height="200" alt="Case_consult" width="612" height="612" /></a></p> <p>The SE® Trauma Institute is privileged to offer a day of case consultations and supervision with author and founder of the Somatic Experiencing® trauma resolution model, Peter A. Levine, PhD.&nbsp;</p> <p>Open to Therapists using body focused approaches, body workers, chiropractors, acupuncturists, nurses, etc. and open to training participants and practitioners of Somatic Experiencing®. The Day is geared for Intermediate students or above, however, Beginners are welcome to present a case or ask questions. Each three hours of consultation time equals one hour credit toward the required eighteen hours for SEP certification. <strong>Remember to bring your session log to receive SEP credit.&nbsp;</strong></p> <blockquote> <p><em>"This is an ideal opportunity to observe Peter modeling his highly creative, intelligent and sensitve healing skills in an intimate and comfortable environment. His demonstrations and explantions furthered my understanding of the myriad of compleixties and simplicities of Somatic Experiencing®. This last supervision with Peter was unforgettable, profound, inspiring and a very encouraging experience for me as a practitioner." </em>Victoria Mihich, MA, MFT, SEP</p> <p>&nbsp;<a href="http://events.constantcontact.com/register/event?llr=qbahuwcab&amp;oeidk=a07e6rljj4m88755a32" title="Constant Contact Event Page - Enroll Now!" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>You can register here. Space is extremely limited.</strong></span></a></p> <p>Please contact Joan Luly for <a href="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/caseconsultflyer1.pdf" target="_blank">more information</a>: <a href="mailto:joansehealing@mac.com">joansehealing@mac.com</a>.</p> <p>If you are interested in having Peter see a client of yours, please contact Justin Snavely at <a href="mailto:traumahealing@gmail.com">traumahealing@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;with the following information:</p> <ol> <li>First name and age of client.</li> <li>Brief list of relevant trauma history (Including the age that it occurred)</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is stuck.</li> <li>Ways in which therapy is advancing.</li> <li>Why do you specifically want Peter to see this client.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <p>NOTE: NO cancellations can be made after January 16th, 2013. Thank you.&nbsp;</p> </blockquote>', 'Peter Levine Group Case Consultation in San Diego - January 19th!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '200-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 200, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/200-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(367, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p><a target="_blank" title="Priscilla Warner\'s blog" href="http://priscillawarnerbooks.com">Priscilla Warner</a>, Author of <em><a title="Her books Amazon page - because we appreciate the free promotion." href="http://www.amazon.com/Learning-Breathe-Yearlong-Quest-Bring/dp/1439181071/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1318165624&amp;sr=1-1">Learning to Breathe</a>&nbsp;</em>was interviewed by Ann Curry on NBC\'s <a target="_blank" title="The Today Show Video timeline - Ms. Warner is at 8:40am Sept 23rd,2011" href="http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/35133959/ns/today/t/watch-latest-today-video/">Today Show</a>, and talked about her book and her year-long journey to overcome anxiety. The subject of trauma came up, and she shared that she used EMDR and "another wonderful, exciting therapy called Somatic Experiencing."&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p> </p> <p>So, we are excited by this very public mention, and present it to you here.&nbsp;</p> <p>Check it out.&nbsp;</p> <p> <object codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=10,0,32,18" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" height="245" width="420"> <param name="FlashVars" value="launch=44638468&amp;width=420&amp;height=245" /> <param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /> <param name="wmode" value="transparent" /> <param name="src" value="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/32545640" /><embed height="245" width="420" src="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/32545640" wmode="transparent" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" flashvars="launch=44638468&amp;width=420&amp;height=245" type="application/x-shockwave-flash"></embed> </object> </p> <p style="font-size: 11px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #999; margin-top: 5px; background: transparent; text-align: center; width: 420px;">Visit msnbc.com for <a style="text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;" href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com">breaking news</a>, <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3032507" style="text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;">world news</a>, and <a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/3032072" style="text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom: 1px dotted #999 !important; font-weight: normal !important; height: 13px; color: #5799db !important;">news about the economy</a></p>', 'Priscilla Warner mentions trauma therapy on Today show', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 189, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/189-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(368, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p><img class=" size-full wp-image-185" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Peterheadshot_twitter.jpg" width="360" height="270" alt="Peterheadshot_twitter" style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial;" width="360" height="270" /> <img class=" size-full wp-image-186" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/vanderkolkportret1.jpg" width="196" height="270" alt="Bessel van der Kolk Pic" style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial;" width="1456" height="2008" /></p> <p><img class=" size-full wp-image-187" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Meadows_plain_2011lg.png" width="500" height="125" alt="Meadows logo" width="864" height="216" /></p> <p>Thanks to The <a style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial; font-size: 16px;" target="_blank" title="The Meadows Homepage" href="http://www.themeadows.org/">Meadows Addiction Treatment Center</a>,&nbsp;Dr. Levine will be doing two events on the Eastern Seaboard this September, based on his best-selling book - In an Unspoken Voice, How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness. He will be joined in Boston by trauma pioneer, Bessel van der Kolk, M.D.</p> <p>These presentations, designed for therapists, but approachable by all, will be a whirlwind tour, starting at the very beginnings of the animal world, through human development and our developing nervous system, onto the ethological connections to trauma. Several case studies and video examples will be shown in this dynamic and exciting events - one of my favorites.&nbsp;</p> <p>Bessel van der Kolk is a premiere researcher on trauma, author of the seminal book <em><a target="_blank" title="Link to Dr. van der Kolk\'s work" href="index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=23:traumatic-stress-the-effects-of-overwhelming-experience-on-mind-body-and-society-by-bessel-a-van-der-kolk&amp;catid=11&amp;Itemid=4">Traumatic Stress</a></em></p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Find info and register for New York" href="http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992641">New York City</a>&nbsp;</p> <p>AMA theater on 7th Avenue, will be on September 16.</p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Find info and register for Boston, Mass" href="http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992653">Boston</a></p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Find info and register for Boston, Mass" href="http://www.regonline.com/builder/site/Default.aspx?EventID=992653"></a>featuring Bessel van der Kolk, author of the seminal book, Traumatic Stress, &nbsp;September 23rd.</p> <p> </p>', 'Dr. Levine presents in Boston and NY this September!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '188-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 188, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/188-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
