(379, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p>Dr. Levine, in partnership with <a href="http://www.soundstrue.com/shop/Welcome.do" title="Soundstrue home" target="_blank">Soundstrue, Inc.</a>, has created a online course to help those suffering from the grip of trauma. During this 10 week course, you will be provided with additional content not available from the book, including 3 podcasts, and a variety of video content.&nbsp;</p> <p>{gallery}articles/healing-trauma-course{/gallery}</p>  <!--more-->  <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><a href="http://www.soundstrue.com/shop/SelectProd.do?prodId=2410&amp;manufacturer=Sounds%20True&amp;name=The%20Healing%20Trauma%20Online%20Course" title="Healing Trauma Soundstrue page" target="_blank">From Soundstrue.com</a></p> <p>Evolution has provided us with a way to deal with trauma the moment it happens—yet our cultural training overrides our body’s natural instinct about what to do. The result is that we often store the energy trauma in the body, leading to unexplained physical problems, emotional issues, and psychological blockages. Dr. Peter A. Levine’s breakthrough techniques have helped many thousands of trauma survivors tap into our innate ability to heal—creating profound results where “talking” cures so frequently come up short.</p> <p>With The Healing Trauma Online Course, this respected therapist and teacher presents an online training course in his revolutionary system for releasing the energy of traumatic events and restoring a harmonious balance to the body and mind. Drawing on his clinical research and his study of how animals release trauma, Dr. Levine teaches you each of the essential principles of his four-phase process. You will learn how and where you are storing unresolved distress, how to become more aware of your body’s physiological responses to danger, and specific methods to free yourself from trauma. Now you can address unexplained symptoms at their source—your body—and return to the natural state you were meant to live in. Includes three live Q&amp;A sessions with Dr. Levine.&nbsp;</p> <p><img class=" size-full wp-image-163" alt="healingtrauma-workshop1" height="500" width="500" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/healingtrauma-workshop11.jpg" width="500" height="500" /></p>', 'Healing Trauma Course with Peter A. Levine', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '164-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 164, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/164-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(380, 1, '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '<p style="float: right;"><img class=" size-full wp-image-161" alt="unspoken-voice-cover" height="423" width="250" src="http://localhost:8888/speed/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/unspoken-voice-cover.png" width="250" height="423" /></p> <p>In an Unspoken Voice: How the Body Releases Trauma and Restores Goodness, Peter A Levine, PhD explores the interconnections between evolutionary neurophysiology, animal behavior, and Trauma. Basing this on his over four decades of clinical work, as well as a vast collection of citations from research journals, as well as classic and contemporary literature. Dr. Levine explains, in great depth, dazzling insight and charming humor, about the importance of the basic neurological structures of the "so-called" primitive brain areas in regards to trauma, and how, by using a sensation based approach, this trauma can be healed.&nbsp;</p> <p><a target="_blank" title="Click here to see the preview on Amazon" href="http://www.amazon.com/Unspoken-Voice-Releases-Restores-Goodness/dp/1556439431/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;s=books&amp;qid=1279671408&amp;sr=8-1-catcorr">Preorder from Amazon now and save 33%!</a></p>', 'In an Unspoken Voice arrives September 28th! ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '162-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '2014-05-22 02:31:09', '', 162, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/162-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
