(435, 3, '2014-07-03 22:06:37', '2014-07-03 22:06:37', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSomatic Experiencing® is a body-awareness approach to trauma taught throughout the world.\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nIt is the result of over forty years of observation, research and development by Dr. Levine. Based upon the realization that human beings have an innate ability to overcome the effects of trauma, Somatic Experiencing® has touched the lives of many thousands. SE® restores self-regulation, and returns a sense of aliveness, relaxation and wholeness to traumatized individuals who have had these precious gifts taken away. Dr Levine has applied his work to healing combat veterans, rape survivors, Holocaust survivors, auto accident and post surgical trauma, chronic pain sufferers, and even to infants after traumatic births.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSomaticExperiencing.com is designed to work in conjunction with www. TraumaHealing.com, the primary website for the training, support of health professionals in Somatic Experiencing®, connecting trauma victims to the approximately 5,000 SE® Practitioners across the globe, as well as administrating outreach in the aftermath of natural and man made disasters, and in providing support to underserved populations..\r\n\r\nFrom here, you can learn more about trauma and SE®, find out more about Peter, his latest writing projects, his upcoming events, order his new training DVD’s, and sign up for information for his future workshops and consultations. You will also find links that will redirect you towards finding a SE® practitioner, learn about the SE® training program, and find out how to get involved with the Somatic Experiencing Trauma Institute (Formerly the Foundation for Human Enrichment).', 'Meet Peter A Levine, PhD', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '92-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-07-03 22:06:37', '2014-07-03 22:06:37', '', 92, 'http://localhost:8888/speed/92-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
